Live.PluginDescription: Provides the live visits log and lets you watch your visitors live in the real-time dashboard widget. A visitor profile can be browsed for any given user.
Live.DisableVisitorProfileDescription: All visits-log related features always function.
Live.DisableVisitsLogAndProfile: Turn off visits log and visitor profiles
Live.DisableVisitsLogAndProfileDescription: Also removes features that depend on these, like the e-commerce log, the segmented visits-log, the real-time map or the real-time widget. May be required to comply with local privacy laws/guidelines.
Live.QueryMaxExecutionTimeExceeded: Could not run the query in time.
Live.QueryMaxExecutionTimeExceededReasonDateR: Maybe the selected date range is too wide?
Live.QueryMaxExecutionTimeExceededReasonSegme: Maybe the selected segment didn't match any visits?
Live.QueryMaxExecutionTimeExceededReasonUnkno: Please try again. Get in touch with your administrator or support if the problem persists.
Live.VisitorLogDocumentation: This table shows the latest visits within the selected date range. Hover over the date of a vist to find out when the most recent one occured. %1$s If the date range includes today, you can see your visitors in real-time. %2$s The data displayed here is always live, regardless of whether and how often you make use of the archiving cron-job.
Live.VisitorLogNoDataMessagePurged: The data has likely been purged because the regular deletion of old raw data is on, and the date for this report is more than %s days old. A superuser can change this setting by going to Administration → Privacy.

Live.VisitSummaryWithActionDetails: Spent a total of %1$s%2$s on the website%3$s, and performed %4$s actions%5$s (%6$s) in %7$s visits%8$s.

Live.RowActionTooltipWithDimension: Show the visits log segmented by this %s
Live.SegmentedVisitorLogTitle: Visits log showing visits where %1$s is "%2$s"

Live.OnClickStart: %s is stopped. Click to start it.

Live.VisitorLogSubcategoryHelp1: The visits log shows you every visit your website receives in detail. Find out which actions each visitor has performed, how they got to your site, a bit about who they are, and more (while still complying with your local privacy regulations).
Live.VisitorLogSubcategoryHelp2: While other reports in Matomo show how your visitors behave at an aggregate level, the visits log provides granular detail. You can also use segments to narrow it down to specific types of visits to understand your visitors better.
Live.VisitorLogSubcategoryHelp3: Learn more in the visit-log guide.
Live.RealTimeHelp1: The visits in the real-time report show the real-time flow of visits to your website. It includes a real-time counter of your visits and page views in the last 24 hours and the previous 30 minutes.
Live.RealTimeHelp2: This report refreshes every 5 seconds and displays new visits (or existing visitors that view a new page) at the top of the list with a fade-in effect.
